    "recap_headline": "Davidson College Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PHILADELPIA \u2014 Three La Salle pitchers combined for a no-hitter in a 10-1 series-clinching win over Davidson at DeVincent Field Sunday afternoon.\nWith their second loss of the weekend, the Wildcats fell to 10-11 overall and 2-4 in the Atlantic 10.\nIt's the first no-hitter the Wildcats have been involved in since April 13, 2012, when Wildcats freshman Henry Sisson threw one in a 1-0 win over Wofford.\nLa Salle pitchers Kross Howarth (3.2 IP, 5 Ks), Josh Beck (2.1 IP, 2 Ks) and Titus Shay (3.0 IP, 6 Ks) combined for the no-hitter.\nFour Wildcats reached base Sunday, all via walks and all in the fourth inning.\nMatthew Vannoy\n,\nJamie Daly\nand\nAnthony Torreso\nloaded the bases with consecutive walks, and after two outs were recorded,\nTheo Loughlin's\nbase-on-balls brought in Vannoy.\nLa Salle (11-12, 2-4) built a 6-0 lead through three innings, highlighted by a four-run second.\nUp Next\nThe Wildcats visit Winthrop Tuesday evening.",
